
[1]infantry

   IN'FANTRY, n. In military affairs,the soldiers or troops that serve on
   foot, as distinguished from cavalry; as a company,regiment or brigade
   of infantry. In some armies, there have been heavy-armed infantry, and
   light-armed or light infantry, according to their manner of arming and
   equipping.
